  {
    "id": "koc2012-q073",
    "type": "true_false",
    "topic": "computer-architecture",
    "subtopic": "stack-pointer",
    "stem": "The function of stack pointer is to hold the data currently being worked on.",
    "options": [
      {
        "label": "A",
        "text": "True",
        "isCorrect": false
      },
      {
        "label": "B",
        "text": "False",
        "isCorrect": true
      }
    ],
    "answerOptionLabels": [
      "B"
    ],
    "explanation": "False. The stack pointer holds the address of the top of the stack, a pointer, not the data itself. The register that holds the data currently being worked on is the accumulator or a general-purpose register.",
    "source": {
      "file": "KOC 2012 EXAM (2).pdf",
      "exam": "KOC",
      "tier": "gold",
      "year": 2012,
      "originalNumber": 73
    },
    "keyProvenance": "inline_bold",
    "keyVerified": true,
    "verificationLevel": "double",
    "needsReview": false,
    "flags": [],
    "dedupeHash": "b75192c0387679963339ed8fa6109843817cc6df"
  },
  {
    "id": "koc2012-q074",
    "type": "mcq",
    "topic": "computer-architecture",
    "subtopic": "cpu-components",
    "stem": "The CPU components are:",
    "options": [
      {
        "label": "A",
        "text": "Memory & ALU",
        "isCorrect": false
      },
      {
        "label": "B",
        "text": "Register & Memory",
        "isCorrect": false
      },
      {
        "label": "C",
        "text": "ALU & Control Unit",
        "isCorrect": true
      }
    ],
    "answerOptionLabels": [
      "C"
    ],
    "explanation": "The CPU consists of the ALU (which computes) and the control unit (which fetches and decodes instructions and directs the other units), plus registers. Main memory is the trap: it is external to the CPU and sits on the other side of the bus, so any option containing 'Memory' is wrong.",
    "source": {
      "file": "KOC 2012 EXAM (2).pdf",
      "exam": "KOC",
      "tier": "gold",
      "year": 2012,
      "originalNumber": 74
    },
    "keyProvenance": "inline_bold",
    "keyVerified": true,
    "verificationLevel": "double",
    "needsReview": false,
    "flags": [],
    "dedupeHash": "1497fc3bc254c1027653b2a2c41f364a6e6607a0"
  },
  {
    "id": "koc2012-q075",
    "type": "mcq",
    "topic": "computer-architecture",
    "subtopic": "cpu-components",
    "stem": "Component of a computer that executes programs stored in memory is:",
    "options": [
      {
        "label": "A",
        "text": "CPU",
        "isCorrect": true
      },
      {
        "label": "B",
        "text": "Accumulator",
        "isCorrect": false
      },
      {
        "label": "C",
        "text": "Register",
        "isCorrect": false
      }
    ],
    "answerOptionLabels": [
      "A"
    ],
    "explanation": "The CPU is the component that fetches instructions from memory and executes them. The accumulator and registers are sub-parts inside the CPU, so they are too narrow to be the component that 'executes programs'.",
    "source": {
      "file": "KOC 2012 EXAM (2).pdf",
      "exam": "KOC",
      "tier": "gold",
      "year": 2012,
      "originalNumber": 75
    },
    "keyProvenance": "inline_bold",
    "keyVerified": true,
    "verificationLevel": "double",
    "needsReview": false,
    "flags": [],
    "dedupeHash": "dac36b3197f10777b736ec64ff0d0b6460046c8f"
  },
  {
    "id": "koc2012-q076",
    "type": "mcq",
    "topic": "computer-architecture",
    "subtopic": "word-size",
    "stem": "Number of bytes in word of 16 bit computers is:",
    "options": [
      {
        "label": "A",
        "text": "2 bytes",
        "isCorrect": true
      },
      {
        "label": "B",
        "text": "8 bytes",
        "isCorrect": false
      },
      {
        "label": "C",
        "text": "16 bytes",
        "isCorrect": false
      }
    ],
    "answerOptionLabels": [
      "A"
    ],
    "explanation": "A byte is 8 bits, so a 16-bit word is 16 / 8 = 2 bytes. The trap is answering '16 bytes' by copying the number out of the stem without converting bits to bytes.",
    "source": {
      "file": "KOC 2012 EXAM (2).pdf",
      "exam": "KOC",
      "tier": "gold",
      "year": 2012,
      "originalNumber": 76
    },
    "keyProvenance": "inline_bold",
